{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TeGENN1iyGxnM2aHRUMwPz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: STEP 03 Vendor Spend Analysis Results\n     3→description: STEP 03 vendor spend analysis results (top 10, spend tiers, key observations); use in STEP 09 strategy recommendations\n     4→type: project\n     5→---\n     6→\n     7→## Summary Statistics\n     8→\n     9→- **Total vendors:** 386\n    10→- **Total 12-month spend:** $7,887,360.40\n    11→- **Largest vendor:** Salesforce UK ($3,117,225.89 — 39.5% of total)\n    12→- **Smallest vendor:** Coles ($17.51)\n    13→\n    14→## Spend Tiers\n    15→\n    16→| Tier | Vendors | Total Spend | % of Total |\n    17→|------|---------|-------------|------------|\n    18→| High Spend (>$200K) | 5 | $4,290,787 | 54.4% |\n    19→| Medium Spend ($50K–$200K) | 21 | $1,956,559 | 24.8% |\n    20→| Low Spend (<$50K) | 360 | $1,640,014 | 20.8% |\n    21→\n    22→## Top 10 Vendors by Spend\n    23→\n    24→| Rank | Vendor | Spend (USD) | % of Total |\n    25→|------|--------|-------------|------------|\n    26→| 1 | Salesforce UK Ltd-UK | $3,117,225.89 | 39.5% |\n    27→| 2 | Navan (Tripactions Inc) | $357,983.62 | 4.5% |\n    28→| 3 | BDO LLP | $343,081.39 | 4.3% |\n    29→| 4 | TOG UK Properties Limited | $263,821.16 | 3.3% |\n    30→| 5 | Cloudcrossing BVBA | $208,675.15 | 2.6% |\n    31→| 6 | Zagrebtower D.O.O. | $183,754.42 | 2.3% |\n    32→| 7 | Innovent Spaces Private Limited | $147,347.80 | 1.9% |\n    33→| 8 | Weking D.O.O. | $144,093.20 | 1.8% |\n    34→| 9 | Jensten Insurance Brokers | $142,699.73 | 1.8% |\n    35→| 10 | GPT Space & Co | $133,506.78 | 1.7% |\n    36→| | **Top 10 Total** | **$5,042,188** | **63.9%** |\n    37→\n    38→## High-Spend Strategic Vendors (>$200K) — All flagged Optimize\n    39→\n    40→1. Salesforce UK Ltd-UK — $3,117,225.89 — Sales\n    41→2. Navan (Tripactions Inc) — $357,983.62 — G&A\n    42→3. BDO LLP — $343,081.39 — Finance\n    43→4. TOG UK Properties Limited — $263,821.16 — Facilities\n    44→5. Cloudcrossing BVBA — $208,675.15 — Engineering\n    45→\n    46→## Suggestion Breakdown\n    47→\n    48→| Suggestion | Vendors | Spend |\n    49→|------------|---------|-------|\n    50→| Optimize | 25 | $6,189,417 |\n    51→| Terminate | 344 | $1,552,621 |\n    52→| Consolidate | 17 | $145,322 |\n    53→\n    54→## Key Observations for Step 09\n    55→\n    56→- Salesforce at 39.5% is a critical single-vendor concentration risk\n    57→- Top 10 vendors = 63.9% of spend; top 5 = 54.3%\n    58→- 360 long-tail vendors (<$50K) account for only 20.8% of spend — high overhead, low value\n    59→- 344 Terminate vendors = $1.55M savings opportunity\n    60→- 17 Consolidate vendors = $145K across duplicate relationships (Navan/Tripactions, Apple entities, Bupa entities, Acclime, DHL, HRSolution, TM Forum, Allianz)\n    61→\n    62→**Why:** Results from STEP 03 analysis of the Vendor Analysis Assessment sheet (386 vendors, $7,887,360.40 total spend).\n    63→**How to apply:** Use these figures as the factual basis for STEP 09 strategy recommendations on optimization, termination, and consolidation targets.\n    64→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6052fd6a-0825-4d0d-b821-8264b77b2b81","uuid":"c78e2777-4e48-4e83-89af-fe17490f0803","timestamp":"2026-03-20T21:34:07.319Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\rjega\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-rjega-vendor-spend-analysis\\memory\\project_vendor_spend_analysis.md","content":"---\nname: STEP 03 Vendor Spend Analysis Results\ndescription: STEP 03 vendor spend analysis results (top 10, spend tiers, key observations); use in STEP 09 strategy recommendations\ntype: project\n---\n\n## Summary Statistics\n\n- **Total vendors:** 386\n- **Total 12-month spend:** $7,887,360.40\n- **Largest vendor:** Salesforce UK ($3,117,225.89 — 39.5% of total)\n- **Smallest vendor:** Coles ($17.51)\n\n## Spend Tiers\n\n| Tier | Vendors | Total Spend | % of Total |\n|------|---------|-------------|------------|\n| High Spend (>$200K) | 5 | $4,290,787 | 54.4% |\n| Medium Spend ($50K–$200K) | 21 | $1,956,559 | 24.8% |\n| Low Spend (<$50K) | 360 | $1,640,014 | 20.8% |\n\n## Top 10 Vendors by Spend\n\n| Rank | Vendor | Spend (USD) | % of Total |\n|------|--------|-------------|------------|\n| 1 | Salesforce UK Ltd-UK | $3,117,225.89 | 39.5% |\n| 2 | Navan (Tripactions Inc) | $357,983.62 | 4.5% |\n| 3 | BDO LLP | $343,081.39 | 4.3% |\n| 4 | TOG UK Properties Limited | $263,821.16 | 3.3% |\n| 5 | Cloudcrossing BVBA | $208,675.15 | 2.6% |\n| 6 | Zagrebtower D.O.O. | $183,754.42 | 2.3% |\n| 7 | Innovent Spaces Private Limited | $147,347.80 | 1.9% |\n| 8 | Weking D.O.O. | $144,093.20 | 1.8% |\n| 9 | Jensten Insurance Brokers | $142,699.73 | 1.8% |\n| 10 | GPT Space & Co | $133,506.78 | 1.7% |\n| | **Top 10 Total** | **$5,042,188** | **63.9%** |\n\n## High-Spend Strategic Vendors (>$200K) — All flagged Optimize\n\n1. Salesforce UK Ltd-UK — $3,117,225.89 — Sales\n2. Navan (Tripactions Inc) — $357,983.62 — G&A\n3. BDO LLP — $343,081.39 — Finance\n4. TOG UK Properties Limited — $263,821.16 — Facilities\n5. Cloudcrossing BVBA — $208,675.15 — Engineering\n\n## Suggestion Breakdown\n\n| Suggestion | Vendors | Spend |\n|------------|---------|-------|\n| Optimize | 25 | $6,189,417 |\n| Terminate | 344 | $1,552,621 |\n| Consolidate | 17 | $145,322 |\n\n## Key Observations for Step 09\n\n- Salesforce at 39.5% is a critical single-vendor concentration risk\n- Top 10 vendors = 63.9% of spend; top 5 = 54.3%\n- 360 long-tail vendors (<$50K) account for only 20.8% of spend — high overhead, low value\n- 344 Terminate vendors = $1.55M savings opportunity\n- 17 Consolidate vendors = $145K across duplicate relationships (Navan/Tripactions, Apple entities, Bupa entities, Acclime, DHL, HRSolution, TM Forum, Allianz)\n\n**Why:** Results from STEP 03 analysis of the Vendor Analysis Assessment sheet (386 vendors, $7,887,360.40 total spend).\n**How to apply:** Use these figures as the factual basis for STEP 09 strategy recommendations on optimization, termination, and consolidation targets.\n","numLines":64,"startLine":1,"totalLines":64}}}
